The paper deals with counting problems in discrete structures (matroids) and uses techniques from combinatorial optimization, convex optimization, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
